"{\"content\":{\"body\":\" **前言：**翻译角是风哥介绍海外加密社区优秀文章的窗口，做这部分工作一方面是为提升个人视野，另一方面是为提升英文阅读与翻译能力，可预见的未来，币圈将成为英语匮乏者的荒漠，不持续进化的人将被淘汰出局。另外，如遇优秀项目，也会对项目白皮书进行翻译与介绍。需要说明的是，翻译的这些文章不一定取得原作者同意，但会对作者进行背景调查与文字介绍，这些介绍与广告无关。本文是知名加密研究机构Messari一年一度的年度总结，由于篇幅较长，**我将分30次分发**。\\n\\n \\n\\n**本文作者**：Ryan Selkis@twobitidiot\\n\\n**原文标题**：Messari Report Crypto Theses for 2022\\n\\n**原文链接**：<https://messari.io/pdf/messari-report-crypto-theses-for-2022.pdf>\\n\\n**发布时间**：2021年12月4日\\n\\n**阅读提示：**下划线词组代表引用链接部分，**黑色加粗代表重点单词与词组。**\\n\\n \\n\\n![](https://images.mirror-media.xyz/publication-images/hKrwH_kk9L1YEp8yDsV9B.png?height=1020&width=2016)\\n\\n**正文（02）：**\\n\\n \\n\\n# 十大叙事与投资主题\\n\\n \\n\\n## 1、制度信任的破产\\n\\nWhy are you reading this?\\n\\n为什么你会阅读这篇报告？\\n\\n \\n\\nMaybe you’re among the nearly half of Millennials and Gen X investors\\\\[1\\\\] who said it would “take a miracle” to retire. You’re **worried about skyrocketing public debt\\\\[2\\\\]**, not-so-**transitory** inflation\\\\[3\\\\], and what happens when we finally experience a **hike** in interest rates\\\\[4\\\\]. For you, crypto is a life raft.\\n\\n\\\\[1\\\\]<https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2021-09-15/401k-savings-retirement-wealthy-investors-wonder-how-much-is-enough>\\n\\n\\\\[2\\\\]<https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2021-09-08/u-k-blinks-first-on-covid-deficits-as-sunak-pushes-tax-increase>\\n\\n\\\\[3\\\\]<https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2021-08-31/fed-now-risks-too-slow-taper-after-too-fast-in-2013-rajan-says>\\n\\n\\\\[4\\\\]<https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2021-09-08/u-s-stocks-cut-to-underweight-at-morgan-stanley-on-higher-risk>\\n\\n也许你是占总人口一半的千禧一代与X一代的投资者，你可能会说顺利退休需要奇迹，你可能会担心飞速增长的公共债务，持续不断的通货膨胀，以及当利率最终大幅上涨时我们将会经历什么。那么对你而言，加密世界就是诺亚方舟。\\n\\n \\n\\nMaybe you’re one of the 70% of Americans who **disapprove** of Congress\\\\[1\\\\] and no longer trust policymakers to do the right thing given that they spend **recklessly**\\\\[2\\\\] and insider trade with **impunity**\\\\[3\\\\]. You’re looking for an **alternative** to central planners in DC and Beijing. For you, crypto is an exit vote.\\n\\n\\\\[1\\\\]<https://www.statista.com/statistics/207579/public-approval-rating-of-the-us-congress/>\\n\\n\\\\[2\\\\]<https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2021-10-07/the-extremely-serious-case-for-minting-the-1-trillion-coin>\\n\\n\\\\[3\\\\]<https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2021-10-04/fed-s-internal-watchdog-to-open-review-into-trading-activity>\\n\\n也许你是美国那70%的不赞同国会，不再相信决策者会做正确事情的美国人之一，认为他们毫无节制地花钱，不受惩罚地进行内幕交易，你正在寻找华盛顿决策者的替代方案，那么对你而言，加密就是一个退出票。\\n\\n \\n\\nMaybe you’re a **populist** - from the right or the left - that seethes knowing Wall Street faced no **repercussions** for **fueling** the last **financial crisis**, and tends to profit from federal policies that punish their customers. Or you’re worried about Big Tech’s **monopoly power**, **censorship**, and control over your personal data. For you, crypto is **a shot across their bows**.\\n\\n也许你是一个民粹主义者——不管是右派还是左派——深知华尔街不会受到任何影响继续为上一次金融危机火上浇油而深感愤怒，同时还往往从惩罚其客户的联邦政策中获利。或你担心大科技公司的垄断权力、审查制度和对你个人数据的控制。对你而言，crypto是对他们的严重警告！\\n\\n \\n\\n![](https://images.mirror-media.xyz/publication-images/iE9JiBXLWUXRH_0tG3P69.png?height=680&width=825)\\n\\n*来源：A16z: How to Win the Future*[ https://a16z.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/How-to-Win-the-Future-Deck.pdf](https://a16z.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/How-to-Win-the-Future-Deck.pdf)\\n\\n \\n\\nOf course, you could just be into crypto for the fast money, memes, and jpegs. That’s cool, too.\\n\\n当然，你可以为赚快钱而进入加密行业，memes与jpegs都会是不错的选择。\\n\\n \\n\\nWhether you’re here as a **missionary** or a **mercenary**, you’ll find that one of the primary **unifying forces** behind this movement is the belief that decentralized technologies with **embedded financial incentives** (a good shorthand for Web3) **offer a compelling, often lucrative, alternative** to our **decaying legacy institutions**.\\n\\n无论你是加密信仰者还是投机分子，这场运动背后的主要团结力量是对于具有嵌入式激励机制（简称web3）的去中心化技术的信仰，web3为腐朽的机构提供了一个引人入胜的/有利可图的替代方案。\\n\\n \\n\\nThat brings me to my first prediction for 2022: things will get worse before they get better in the “real” world. Inflation will remain above 5% throughout 2022 (70% confidence), while late year interest rate hikes **stall the stock market’s momentum** and hurt growth stocks (60% confidence the S&P dips next year). That will be good for crypto short-term, but risky in the medium-term, as more crypto companies and their users get **deplatformed** and **censorship** from western tech and banking platforms **accelerates** **amidst** the Biden administration’s crypto **crackdown**.\\n\\n这带来了我对2022年的第一个预测：现实世界将会变得越来越糟糕，整个2022年通货膨胀将会维持在5%以上（70%的信心），与此同时明年年末的利率上涨将会抑制股市的上涨势头，并会对成长型股票造成伤害，明年标普指数将会下跌（60%的信心）。在拜登的加密镇压计划也会加速西方科技企业与银行针对加密公司与用户的审查与去平台化，短期而言这对加密市场是好事，但长期而言意味着风险。\\n\\n \\n\\n## 2. 加密与Web3终将到来\\n\\nThat’s one of the only **bearish predictions** in this report. Crypto, or the recently en vogue “Web3”, is an unstoppable force in the long-term.\\n\\n这是本报告中仅有的悲观预测。加密，或者说最近流行的“Web3”，是一股长期不可阻挡的力量。\\n\\n \\n\\nChris Dixon calls it\\\\[1\\\\] “the internet owned by the builders and users, **orchestrated** with tokens.” Eshita describes the Web1 -> Web2 -> Web3 evolution as Read-Only -> Read-Write -> Read-Write-Own\\\\[2\\\\]. Regardless of your preferred **shorthand**, it might seem **intuitive** that the **user-owned** economy will **outperform** the **monopolist-owned** economy in the long-term.\\n\\n\\\\[1\\\\]<https://future.a16z.com/why-web3-matters/>\\n\\n\\\\[2\\\\]<https://eshita.mirror.xyz/H5bNIXATsWUv_QbbEz6lckYcgAa2rhXEPDRkecOlCOI>\\n\\nChris Dixon称之为“网络建设者们将通过精心设计的token掌控对互联网的控制权”，Eshita将互联网的变革过程描述成Web1 -> Web2 -> Web3，即从只读-> 读写 -> 读写并拥有。直觉认为，不管你喜欢的速记方式是什么，从长远来看，用户掌控的经济将优于垄断者拥有的经济。\\n\\n \\n\\nThere’s a lot to unpack over the course of this report, but the general **theme** is consistent: we’re going from an internet built on “rented land”\\\\[1\\\\] with **monopoly overlords**, to **an infinite frontier** of new possibilities. On the frontier, crypto presents a credible revolution\\\\[2\\\\] to all monopolies, which is why its inevitability scares the incumbents.\\n\\n\\\\[1\\\\]<https://twitter.com/eshita/status/1410719809398972416>\\n\\n\\\\[2\\\\]<https://twitter.com/0xangus/status/1450399059529842691?s=21>\\n\\n尽管想要通过本报告有很多揭开很多谜底，但还是会坚守一个总体的叙事原则：我们正从一个建立在租借地之上、拥有垄断大领主的互联网，走向无限可能性的疆土中。在另一个疆土中，加密世界对垄断分子呈现出的可信革命，让任何在任者的恐惧都不可避免地达到极值。\\n\\n \\n\\nWe have all the key ingredients we need to succeed.\\n\\n 我们拥有成功所需的所有关键要素。 \\n\\n \\n\\n1）Talent: Brilliant, passionate, big-visioned young builders are flocking to the open design space of crypto in record numbers\\\\[1\\\\], often on their nights and weekends\\\\[2\\\\].\\n\\n2）Capital: We’ve seen **mammoth** venture capital fund raises, crypto startup fundraises, and **staggering** growth in emerging **liquid protocols** across Web3 use cases.\\n\\n3）Timing: **Critical infrastructure** was installed during the last bear market that made it easier than ever (**socially and practically**) to embrace this techno-political movement.\\n\\n\\\\[1\\\\]<https://www.paradigm.xyz/2021/09/the-community-garden-the-case-for-leaving-faang-companies-for-crypto/>\\n\\n\\\\[2\\\\]<https://cdixon.mirror.xyz/brEszs7HBGmEWouspL8QUm5g68Ppb7kRrkRjbD1T0Zg>\\n\\n1）人才：聪慧过人、思想开放、视野广阔的年轻建设者们常常在下班之后或者节假日，集中精力在这个完全开放的加密空间，参与人数也在创纪录地增长。\\n\\n2）资本：我们看到大量风险资本被募集，大量加密创业基金被成立，以及Web3使用案例中新兴流动协议的惊人增长。\\n\\n3）时机：在上一轮熊市中，关键的基础设施得以建设，这使得无论是社会还是现实层面，都比以往任何时候更容易拥抱这场技术政治运动。\\n\\n \\n\\nIn a recent post from Eric Peters at One River Capital, he argued that we live in a period of **social upheaval**, where young people are **keen to** invest in technologies that **disrupt** (and **potentially bankrupt**) older generations’ preferred institutions, while pushing investments that benefit themselves at the **expense of the old guard**. The best part about being young and broke, he says, is that “you have little to lose.” That’s especially true when younger people **view legacy institutions as exploitative**.\\n\\n在Eric Peters近期在一江资本（One River Capital）的报告中，他认为我们正生存在一个动荡的时代，年轻人热衷于投资那些能够破坏老一代人首选机构的技术，同时推动以牺牲老一辈人利益为代价的投资。他说，年轻与破产最大的好处在于，你也没什么可失去的了。当年轻人将遗产机构视为剥削性机构时，尤为甚。\\n\\n \\n\\nDeFi offers savers 5% vs. Wall Street’s 0.5%. Non-fungible tokens (“NFTs”) give creators **monetization** opportunities without Hollywood’s 50%+ rents. Open games and social graphs remove the 100% take rate from tech incumbents and eliminate deplatforming risks.\\n\\nDeFi年化5%，而华尔街只给你0.5%。NFTs给了创造者变现的机会，却不需要好莱坞50%+的租金。开放式游戏和社交图表消除了现有科技公司100%的收购率，消除了脱平台风险。 \\n\\n \\n\\nI have 99% conviction that crypto will be an **order of magnitude** larger by 2030 because the user economics here are an **order of magnitude** more attractive. We’re at the **brink** of a total transformation of the global economy. One that’s bigger than mobile, and maybe even the internet itself.\\n\\n我敢肯定，到2030年，加密世界将会呈数量级扩大，因为这里的用户经济更具吸引力。我们正处于全球经济转型的关键时期，我们要迎接一个比手机，甚至比互联网本身更大的经济系统的到来。\\n\\n \\n\\nThough I **waffle** on where we are in this particular cycle, the tail winds remain strong and the **capital markets flush**. So my probabilities are split among three scenarios: 1) most likely, we experience a blow off top before the end of Q1 2021, followed by a shallower, but still painful multi-year bear market; 2) we rocket to a $20 trillion bubble that lasts all year, and sits on par with the dotcom boom in real dollars - unlikely, but possible given accommodative monetary policies worldwide, neverending government spending, and crypto’s accelerating narrative momentum; 3) we march slowly and steadily higher into **perpetuity** (the “supercycle” thesis).\\n\\n尽管我在这一特定周期中含糊其辞地谈论了我们所处的位置，但尾风依然强劲，资本市场繁荣。因此，我将可能性分为以下三种：1）最有可能的是，我们在2021Q1结束之前经历了一次冲顶，随后是一个较浅但仍然痛苦的多年熊市；2）我们膨胀到20万亿美元的泡沫，持续一整年，与真正的互联网繁荣不太可能，但可能是全球范围内宽松的货币政策，无休止的政府支出，以及密码加速的叙事势头；3） 我们的牛市缓慢而稳定地迈向永恒（“超级周期”理论）。 \\n\\n \\n\\n**Ironically**, the **most bearish case** here (Q1 blow-off top) may be the **most bullish** long-term and vice versa. “**Hyperbitcoinization**” and crypto’s permanent ascendance at this stage of our development would only happen against a very **dystopian** backdrop indeed.\\n\\n具有讽刺意味的是，这里最悲观的情况（第一季度到顶）可能是最乐观的，反之亦然。在当下我们人类所处的发展阶段，“超级比特币化”和加密技术的永恒优势，确实只能在反人类、极权政府、生态灾难与其他社会性的灾难性（反乌托邦，dystopian）的背景下发生。 \\n\\n \\n\\n \\n\\n## 3、桥/NFT/DAO\\n\\n“Web3” is a good **all-encompassing** term that **captures** cryptocurrencies (digital gold & stablecoins), smart contract computing (Layer 1-2 platforms), decentralized hardware **infrastructure** (video, storage, **sensors**, etc), Non-Fungible Tokens (digital ID & property rights), DeFi (financial services to swap and **collateralize** web3 assets), the Metaverse (the digital **commons** built in game-like environments), and community governance (DAOs, or decentralized autonomous organizations).\\n\\n \\n\\nWeb3是一个包罗万象的词条，他涵盖了加密货币（数字黄金与稳定币），智能合约（L1/L2平台），去中心化硬件基础设施（无线电/存储器/传感器等），NFT（数字ID与财产权），DeFi（金融服务交易/web3抵押资产），元宇宙（建立在类游戏化环境下的数字居民），社区治理（DAOs，去中心化自治组织）。\\n\\n \\n\\nI expect growth everywhere across Web3, though three areas are particularly underdeveloped: NFT infrastructure, DAO tooling, and **inter-protocol** bridges.\\n\\n我期待Web3能够在任何地方成长起来，尽管有三个领域不是特别发达，他们是：NFT基础设施/DAO工具/协议间的桥。\\n\\n \\n\\nWe’re witnessing a Cambrian explosion of innovation within the NFT space that is just getting started. I’m not sure how much longer the market for individual NFTs can bubble up, but I do know that **reliable** and **ubiquitous** NFT tooling is still largely missing. Marketplaces, financialization primitives, creator tools, **community-oriented** business models, and decentralized **identity management/reputation management systems** are all in their infancy. That core infrastructure will be one of the hottest areas of investment in 2022.\\n\\n我们正在��证NFT领域的创新就像寒武纪生物大爆炸一般的创新，这仅仅是开始。我不确定个人NFT泡沫的破裂还有多久，但是可靠的且通用的NFT工具一直都有巨大的缺口。与NFT相关的市场/金融化原语/创造者工具/面向社区的商业模型/以及去中心化的身份管理与名誉管理系统都处于原始阶段。与NFT相关的核心基础设施的建设，将会成为2022年投资领域最热的区域。\\n\\n \\n\\nSame goes for DAO tooling, which is an existential need right now across crypto communities, where voter **apathy** is reaching crisis levels and investments are taking far too long to process. If you take the 10 year view that open, token-governed marketplaces will replace companies (as I do); and recognize that their communities will need 100x improvements in **collaboration** tools in order to operate more efficiently than\\n\\ncentralized competitors; and understand that every DAO treasury transaction is **essentially** subject to a board-level proxy vote today; then you can appreciate why 2022 will be the year of DAO tools. (I’ve bet on it both with my personal portfolio, and via Messari’s bet-the-company move to build an operating system for Web3 participation.)\\n\\nDAO工具也面临相同的问题，整个加密社区都亟需在当下解决这个问题，因为投票者的冷漠正触及危险，投资者也难以推动这一进程。如果你往前看10年，就会发现代币治理将会取代公司治理（就像我所做的），同时也会意识到他们的社区协作工具需要扩张100倍，这样才能够比中心化公司表现的更加高效，也会理解每一个DAO的国库转账都要经过一次董事会级别的投票，然后你就会理解为什么2022年会是DAO治理工具之年。（我已经通过个人投资组合，并通过Messari的公司赌注协议参与建立了一个Web3操作系统协议）。\\n\\n \\n\\nLast but not least, we have the core crypto plumbing: scaling and interoperability solutions. Ethereum’s blockchain hit its capacity this year. Other Layer 1 platforms have exploded 50-100x in value as investors bet on crypto development to parallelize across new ecosystems and **absorb the excess demand**. All of these new blockchains (plus Ethereum’s Layer 2 rollups) will need to talk to each other, so the most acute pain point in crypto today may be the lack of bridges. **If the future is multi-chain, then those who build better cross-chain connectors and help move assets fluidly across parachains, zones, and rollups will inherit the (virtual) earth.**\\n\\n最后不能不提的是，我们拥有核心的加密管道：可扩展性和互操作性解决方案。以太坊今年达到了性能极限。随着投资者押注加密技术开发，以实现新生态系统的并行化，并吸收过剩的需求，其他第1层平台的价值激增50-100倍。 其他Layer 1平台价值激增50-100倍。所有这些新区块链（加上以太坊的第2层汇总）都需要相互沟通，因此加密技术目前最严重的痛点可能是缺少桥梁。如果未来是多链的，那么那些构建更好的跨链连接器并帮助跨副链、分区和汇总流畅地移动资产的人将继承（虚拟）地球。 \\n\\n \\n\\nIf these all sound like foreign concepts, that’s ok. NFTs (Chapter 6), DAOs (Chapter 9), and Layer 1 Interoperability (Chapter 8) make up a third of this year’s report for a reason.\\n\\n如果这些听起来都像外星概念，那没关系。出于某种原因，NFT（第6章）、DAO（第9章）和第1层互操作性（第8章）占今年报告的三分之一。 \",\"timestamp\":1641177852,\"title\":\"【翻译角】Messari 2021年度加密论文，白话翻译版 Parte 02\"},\"digest\":\"TWBzXru4U50WY8Kr1nW4lcu5MTkeMzjCICnKRdZD7Zw\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0x0Ad33A0c329B8f7E30a9101D84f30719Eb299e99\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"alg\\\":\\\"ES256\\\",\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"1dZMwkXzIm2hLvUC_Eg9B0VAZzFUKP6MY7OcJcKB0x4\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"Aqa0gq48Fo7y8IL3R6KQct25ugdNJc7ez05DHnGm_gw\\\"}\",\"signature\":\"ccnXo2fyV0VQRle4eXjGTQmccgCJAlNNv8cqLRpLRsiX8VRalXYXHDxiOboEYo9MdkkUqwelcQvhJ462kvRQTA\",\"signingKeySignature\":\"0xc392bbaaa854e6e5b57d4e5d251e6170652cec32d6bd4d865a049be6855a9c4330ee3b7b6cd2d836e5c9345eadc6aad7f9d0d2f58fa5b59feb9cb576264247c11c\",\"signingKeyMessage\":\"I authorize publishing on mirror.xyz from this device using:\\n{\\\"alg\\\":\\\"ES256\\\",\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"1dZMwkXzIm2hLvUC_Eg9B0VAZzFUKP6MY7OcJcKB0x4\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"Aqa0gq48Fo7y8IL3R6KQct25ugdNJc7ez05DHnGm_gw\\\"}\",\"algorithm\":{\"name\":\"ECDSA\",\"hash\":\"SHA-256\"}},\"nft\":{},\"version\":\"12-21-2020\",\"originalDigest\":\"TWBzXru4U50WY8Kr1nW4lcu5MTkeMzjCICnKRdZD7Zw\"}"